          "body": "Verses 6-9 reveal that covenant love is sustained not by mystical experience but by relentless verbal repetition embedded in daily life. The words are first *on the heart* (6:6) — internalized — then *taught diligently to the sons* (the verb *shanan* means to *sharpen* or *whet*, suggesting honed, repeated, pointed teaching), then *spoken* in every daily posture (sitting, walking, lying down, rising up). They are then made visible: bound on the hand, on the forehead, written on the doorposts and gates. The pattern moves outward in concentric circles: heart → children → body → home. Later Jewish practice literalized this with *tefillin* (phylacteries) and *mezuzot*, and there is honest scholarly debate whether Moses intended literal or metaphorical observance. Either way, the principle is unmistakable: covenant truth must permeate every layer of life, or it will not survive a single generation."
